_Über Desi_ [reports](http://uberdesi.com/blog/2009/04/27/democracy-desi-
ishtyle/) that according to “a new ruling by The Election Commission of India,
voting officials in certain polling stations are now marking middle fingers
with the purple ink, instead of index fingers.” This has sent vibes across
many bloggers who are trying to analyze what the voters are trying to say
proudly displaying their middle finger marked with purple ink.

